In what will come across as a really shocking development, a Nigerian soldier has been crushed to death in Abeokuta. A Nigerian soldier has lost his life in Ogun state after getting into an incident with a trailer. Local reports show that the sad incident happened in the morning on Friday, August 23 at Iyana Mortuary junction, in Abeokuta, Ogun State. It was gathered that the soldier was on his motorcycle when the trailer suffered a brake failure and rammed into him, killing him instantly. The driver fled the scene immediately but his motor boy was held. Below is a graphic video from the scene of the incident: Graphic: Trailer crushes soldier to death at mortuary junction . . A soldier lost his life, this morning, at Iyana Mortuary, in Abeokuta, Ogun State, after being crushed by a trailer. . . It was gathered that the soldier was on his motorcycle when the trailer suffered a brake failure and rammed into him, killing him instantly. The driver fled the scene immediately but his motor boy was held. [Swipe to view graphic video] A post shared by  Instablog9ja (@instablog9ja) on Aug 23, 2019 at 2:55am PDT Source